The person who gathered our pastries has top tier patience. Hats off to her. She was very friendly.
The woman behind the register could use some tact but she wasn't rude.
The guy who made my coffee?? Omg, please teach this guy some manners. I have never been to this location of Amelie's and have never ordered a drink at any location. After paying I stood near the sink station waiting. He says "what's up". I tell him I'm just waiting. Him (hissy): "I'll call your name, I'll call your name". reviews_data.review_text:
Amélie’s is a staple — a Charlotte institution with genuinely great food. The pastries are excellent, the coffee is solid, and the kitchen clearly knows what it’s doing. But the management and operations are embarrassingly bad.

There’s no online order pickup system. You order ahead thinking it’ll be ready — nope. You show up and your food hasn’t even been started. The café is always empty because by the time your order’s ready, you’ve already wasted your lunch break and have to leave.

The staff seems lost, the process is nonexistent, and there’s zero urgency. It feels like no one’s in charge.

It’s heartbreaking — because with even halfway competent leadership, this place would be unbeatable. Instead, it’s the last place I’ll go if I’m on a schedule.

Love the food. Hate the experience. Do better, Amélie’s.
Beyond beautiful interior as well as the desserts. The chocolate desserts are to die for! If I could eat here everyday I would. They have coffee and food as well.

I've always enjoyed Amélie's food, but this was my first and last time visiting this particular location. The selection of tarts and macaroons we tried were all delicious, but the employee taking our order and checking us out was downright rude. He was extremely impatient, not particularly knowledgeable about the menu, and even said "Just tell me what you want" when I asked a question about the menu.
Wonderful!
This place is incredible! Well worth a stop. It's nothing like I thought it would be, in the best way! Hope to be back next time :)

Nice place to hangout with friends,  study or just to enjoy one of their pies, its worth the long wait

I frequent this location in NoDa & will continue to do so based on great atmosphere and customer service. One night I arrived about twenty minutes until closing; although I came in last minute after work, not once did I feel rushed or uncomfortable. In fact, the employees were very kind and understanding. I ordered a sundried tomato turkey wrap, chips, and some macarons. Everything was delicious as usual, however some desserts are touch and feel. For example, I love their Crookie (croissant cookie) and their Pistachio macarons! On the other hand, their chocolate pudding with chocolate chip layers (that is topped with a chocolate covered strawberry) looks very appetizing but falls short in taste. A lot of the desserts are touch and feel in the sense that some look good and taste mediocre, whereas some look underwhelming but taste delicious. This obviously is based on preference. I’m still going to frequent quite often because trying new items every visit has been fun! Shout out to their amazing staff ✨

My wife and I had the breakfast wrap. It was awful. So dry that it was uneatable. Picture of what remains
I told management and they were very apologetic. Even had the kitchen manager come to table to discuss. They even adjusted the bill and asked it there was anything more they could do.
In my opinion , this is the way to address business concerns They get an “A” for customer service.

When you first walk in you are met with a whimsical scenery of Paris-inspired decor, a macaron inspired modle or a giant half of The Eiffle Tower, and you just know this is going to be a great experience.

The gentleman eho assisted us was knowledgeable and even threw in a suggestion of his own, which sounded fantastic.

I tried the salted caramel brownie, his suggestion. It was delicious with just enough caramel and brownie synergy to make the perfect dessert. I also tried the Marie Antoinette tart. They were delicate and tasteful and had a nice fresh raspberry compote on top. Then I tried the brownie cheesecake tart. This was my favorite one as I'm a sucker for brownies. I tried the Cafe Marcotter, which was heavy and filling, I only had half of the cup because of this. The taste was lovely with the French Vanilla. Finally, I had the Sundried Tomato Turkey Wrap which I felt could have been left off. It was something I could easily make at home, so it was nothing special.

Overall, I give this place a solid A+ for being so damn good!

I’ve been to Amélie’s multiple times, mostly for the macarons or crème brûlée, which are always solid. The pastries are definitely the highlight here! That said, the hot food items and salads don’t quite hit the mark for me, which is why I wouldn’t give it a full five stars. I’ve also noticed an off-putting smell on a couple of visits, though thankfully, that hasn’t been an issue recently. Still, the atmosphere is really cute, and it’s a nice spot to grab a sweet treat.

Amélie's French Bakery & Café offers a delightful culinary experience that truly captures the essence of French indulgence. The food is nothing short of superb — from the buttery, flaky croissants to the decadent pastries that melt in your mouth. Every bite feels like a trip to a charming Parisian pâtisserie.

The atmosphere is quaint and elegant, blending a cozy café charm with upscale European-inspired décor. It's the kind of place where you could linger with a book or chat with friends over cappuccinos in style.

The staff interaction occasionally felt curt, almost as though they were eager to move things along. While efficient, a warmer, more welcoming touch would elevate the experience significantly.

Despite the service hiccup, Amélie’s remains a gem for food lovers seeking an authentic taste of France in a beautiful setting.

I was disappointed to see that they carry few pastry options now.. that used to be the big draw to Amelie's. They were out of what my husband wanted and offered no other similar options. They burned my creme brulee and when I pointed it out to the guy, he basically rolled his eyes at me and offered no solution. Both guys were not very friendly or helpful. I asked for my latte to not be too sweet and, of course, it was too sweet. I certainly will not be back.

Went for breakfast and coffee with my wife earlier this morning between 10 and 11 am. Had a bad experience with the barista. For context, the barista's first language is not English and her accent is very heavy and difficult to understand. I believe she's Eastern European. When she called a name that sounded like mine, I inquired as to whether she called my name and our drink orders but still couldn't understand her. Ultimately, I realized she was referring to my drinks. She rudely slammed my drink on the counter and made an offhand comment about me to a couple standing by waiting for their drink orders. When I asked to speak with the manager, a teenager unfortunately returned who was the manager. I explained my experience but the "manager" was dismissive of the encounter. Up until this encounter, my experience at Amelie's was ok, but now I won't be returning. As a person who's lived in Paris, France, the cuisine is far from French. My experience with the idiotic barista and immature manager felt racialized. Black patrons beware!

Will bring my mother in law when she comes in town.

In all honesty, i loved the old amelies. More corky, food is good and on point.
Love their terminus, always get their Chi latte.
Order the goat cheese chicken baguette.

Still frequent this place often!

reviews_data.review_text: Great tasting pastries.

Great desserts.

However it took them 40 minutes (almost to the minute) to prepare a sandwich with an egg, swiss cheese and tomato. Unfortunately, they didn't tell me about wait at the time of the order, and sunk cost fallacy kept me waiting after 10 minutes - how much longer can it be? When I asked about my order at the 25 minute mark, I was shown the dining room (that was less than half full) and was told they are very busy. At that point it became a matter of principle to me to find out how long it actually takes.

There's nothing wrong with being busy. I just wish they were upfront about it.

Sandwich was nothing to write home about.

Always a great experience! Got the pecan tarte, the crust is very crunchy, I think it would be better warmed but loved the caramelized pecans! The cheesecake brownie was also good, the brownie is so decadent! The “cheesecake” part on top wasn’t my favorite though. Still awesome atmosphere!
This place has a great ambience that transports one to Paris. It has quite a vibe with several Parisian props. Crème brûlée was great.

Wow, it's hard to believe that this is the same place it was before the ownership turned over
The pastries are sparse and, frankly, really unimpressive compared to the original location and owners vision.

That's bad enough, but let me tell you about the employees

I brought a friend in for his first time to Amelies. He was super excited and told the guy at the counter that it was first time in.
The guy responded, and I quote,  "That means *nothing* to me."
When I made small talk about loving the former location, he went on a very angry tirade about how terrible the hours were  and said directly to me - as if I had any input in, or control over this at all - that employees deserve outside lives too.
Well, of course they do. But yelling at two people who just want a croissant ain't gonna help anything.

We just left.
I had also just come in after learning that a friend had passed, so being screamed at by a stranger was especially awful.

Ordinary bland pastries and pissed off employees ?
Never again.

I fell in love with Amelie’s years ago. I recall wishing that they would open a location  in my hometown of Atlanta, GA they did, but it did not last long.

One night while  in Charlotte I made the suggestion that my family and I make a late night run to Amelie’s.  It’s been such a long time since I visited that I did not realize they are in a new location. The new  to me location still gives me the same energy as when I visited years ago. The quirkiness of the decor really makes this place special.

We arrived fairly late- maybe 30 minutes prior to closing. However, we were still able to order everything we wanted. Additionally, the staff still had great attitudes!

Overall I love everything about Amelie’s, the decor, the staff and most importantly the food and drinks. If you have a chance to check this spot out, I highly recommend. You do so!

Took a trip to Charlotte & this was a spot to try when visiting. Never had macaroons before, so I decided to try some and man it was delicious! They had so many variety of flavors ( PB&J is fav) . I also ordered the Buttermilk sausage sandwich…. THE BEST BISCUIT EVERR!
Mediocre food, crappy coffee, high prices and they’re going to ask you for 18-22% tip on the counter for that 🤡Deserts are good though, but there are better coffee shops/bakeries for sure.

Who makes matcha with clots?? That’s insane
Ordered roast beef sandwich and it was mediocre, I can make better at home

Fourth time here, fourth time my food is delayed or made wrong. I waited 45 minutes for a salad and a french dip while AT LEAST 20 people got their orders after me (There were only 2 people in line when I got there, so it wasn’t because they were busy. First they forgot my order, then they did not bring it to the table when they said they would after giving me a number, then when I finally realized my food had been sitting at the counter for a while and my food was cold, I saw they gave me the wrong food.) Really frustrating when you are limited on time. The pastries here are delicious, but the service is lacking. The girl who first took my order was visibly upset and had just cursed at a coworker as I walked up to the register.

i got a lavender macaron, palmier, croissant, and a pistachio coconut latte. the latte, macaron, and croissant were all lovely but the palmier tasted a little stale to me. the woman at the cash register was rude when i asked for a drink recommendation. overall, i liked the vibe and the cafe itself is expansive with some interesting decorations/art

What an eclectic out of the big box place to enjoy yourself. The coffee drinks were especially nice and had a personal touch. I definitely will return as they have the best pastries I have seen in a while. Everything seemed so fresh supposingly because everyone is buying it and they have to keep making it !
I 💓💓💓💓💓💓 this place! My friend and I stumbled upon this sweet place. Good food, little pricey, friendly service. The atmosphere was amazing!

Awesome and unique atmosphere, exquisite baked goods!

I love how unique this place is and how good their pastries, etc. are. I don’t normally like macaroons- but theirs are amazing!
I got some of their little tarts which were delicious.

This is one of my wife’s favorite places!
You seriously don’t want to miss out on this gem!
Came to this lovely place today and  sure glad I did the 2 men working were fast and had great recommendations i will definitely return

El lugar es mágico, tiene muchas opciones, tanto dulces como salado, atienden muy amables, los postres son deliciosos, tiene espacio para estacionar gratis, los postres tiene precio accesibles, un lugar diferente para compartir un buen café.

I was skeptical when my girl wanted to try this place but it was the most solid place I've been to in Charlotte. The crowd was diversified the decor was so perfect the at was wonderful.
Then there was the first omg you have to try the macaroons so go in give it a 10 hands down
Loved the atmosphere and the food was amazing .
I love this bakery! When I visit my son and his wife in Charlotte we have breakfast there.  Everything about it is so enjoyable.  The food, the staff, the decor.  You feel like you’re in Paris!

reviews_data.review_text: I heart this location, my favorite for well over 10 years. Amelies my favorite bakery!
Amazing desserts 🍮, beautiful decor and atmosphere.
Absolutely amazing!  Salted caramel brownie was insane great!
Always great!
Great food and fun, unique environment!

I'd believe the over charging was accidental if it didn't happen so often and at every location. Definitely check your receipts!!! and don't order a bowl of soup it's literally the exact same size as the cup. They have two sizes of bowl one holds the exact same volume as the only size cup they have.  We actually tested it by filling the cup with water and pouring it in the bowl it's the same. Which is also cheating.  My daughter loves to get dressed up and go to Cafe however the ambiance here come best be described as where culture and civility go to die.  So, we've given up on Amelia's this will be our last visit.  I would love to see a more honest and authentic establishment here.
Perfect kind of cafe to work at and enjoy a nice pastry.
The food was delicious, but the service was awful. I don’t remember the cashier name, we just had a lunch on 21st of October at 2pm. She was really rude to us, take it serious please.
Great coffee options and the dessert is delicious. I have never had a bad time here.
Amelie's is awesome and needed. It's a safe place to meet and eat. I love the atmosphere!

reviews_data.review_text: Muy lindo, muy buen servicio al cliente, y la comida deliciosa 😋
NOT WORTH IT. This place is super cute. But I waited 35 minutes for a yogurt parfait that has no fruit in it. It also has nothing special to it.
Lovely little cafe with an eclectic work space and delicious treats and food!
Creative and quirky atmosphere. Service was great. My desserts were packaged with care.

Nutella tart was not too sweet which I loved. Lemon tart was perfect! I also got turkey Brie sandwich. It was delicious 😋 a little sweet from the jam they put. Lots of bizarre and surprising things like chandeliers and huge kitchen gadgets.
Would be back to try more pastries 🥐
Food below average
Life is so beautiful today…cold…but still beautiful;) Tiramisu Latte and Chicken pot pie soup are a match made in heaven!
Delicious pastries and nice environment

Atmosphere is incredible. A great stop for a treat on the way back to the triad area when picking someone up from the airport. Staff was friendly and helpful, despite how I looked stepping off an airplane, which is appreciated. The macaroon was not the best I ever had, but the fruit tart was excellent!
Amelie's is always tasty, I appreciate thr salted caramel brownie always being around and a rotation of macaron flavors to mix it up.
My favorite cafe in Charlotte! Fabulous vibe, friendly staff, chick atmosphere! You’ll love here!!
Great atmosphere and good selections. They lose two stars for requiring that I tip for two coffees when I paid with Apple Pay.

Dessert is my thing, and Amelie's didn't disappoint! Seriously, everything was scrumptious. Visit them!!! (And, I'm a baker who is very particular about the dessert I eat!) I just have to mention how adorbs it is inside. 😍😍😍

We came here for brunch around 1 PM on a Saturday. The line was decently long but we only waited about ten minutes. The staff were knowledgeable and friendly!

We each got a tiramisu latte & split the lemon raspberry tart. I got the cream cheese danish and my friend got the strawberry danish.

The lattes were so creamy & smooth! The tart was creamy and fluffy. The strawberry danish had super fresh strawberries and was drizzled in honey. The cream cheese on both was beautifully rich & the pastry was fluffy with the perfect amount of crisp on the edges.

The macaroon flavors we got were (from top to bottom, left to right): Lavender Lemon, Café au lait, Cookie Dough, RE&B (proceeds toward the Hurricane Helene Fund), PB&J, and Coconut Lime. We weren’t sure of the flavor of the Red, White, & Blue but it reminded of us crunch berries! Super tasty.

Can’t wait to try other items on my next visit!

THIS WAS MY FIRST TIME THERE I LOVE THE INSIDE, IT A BEAUTIFUL PLACE TO HAVE ME AND FRIEND  TO HAVE COFFEE AND FRENCH PASTRY AND FEEL LIKE YOU ON PARIS 🤗, NOW I HAVE A NEW PLACE TO GO TOO🤗,  GOOD JOB.  BB🍵🎂🥐

Its a great place to hang out after dinner and get a dessert or a tea.    5 star for the location and the interior space. update since Google asked me: Saturday night- the pastry section was mostly empty. I am ok with that assuming they bake things fresh and want to avoid wastage but the prices were ridiculous on the scraps that were left.
A delicious, cute little spot for sweet treats ❤️

Got a plethora of items. Fruit tart, macaroons, breakfast wrap, cider, and others. The fruit tart was 10/10! Breakfast wrap was 6/10 and cider tasted like just brown sugar 2/10. The atmosphere tho!!!!!!! Going into the first location really was Alice in wonderland meets France. Very cool very fun! Service staff were nice and prompt. Overall worth a go.
Service could not be slower

Amélie's French Bakery & Café. It's an absolute gem that never fails to impress! During my recent visit, I treated myself to their crème brûlée and fruit tart, and let me tell you, they were both out of this world. The crème brûlée had the perfect caramelized top, giving way to a luscious, velvety custard underneath. And the fruit tart? It was a masterpiece with its buttery, flaky crust and a colorful array of fresh fruits that provided a delightful contrast to the creamy filling.

And let's not forget about their coffee - it's the perfect companion to their desserts, with its rich flavor balancing out the sweetness. Yes, the location might be a bit tricky to find, but trust me, the search is totally worth it. Whenever I'm in Charlotte, Amélie's is a non-negotiable stop for me. The consistently top-notch treats and the cozy atmosphere make it an absolute must-visit!
Great pastries. The coffee could been better. I had cappuccino and it was super weak and watery.
Such a unique café! The interior design is trippy, and the food is so yummy 😋
Amazing place with delicious food.

Loved it to the bits. Charlotte being a new city, Amelie’s was on the top recommendations on the list of things to do. We visited and were thrilled to see the location all jazzed up with different themes. The chandeliers being the main attraction. The place gives a fancy vibe yet simple enough to feel comfortable instantly. The desserts have a good variety and will definitely want to keep going back to try more/all of it… Also, they have very good vegetarian options for meals - which is a huge plus. Definitely a recommended spot if you are in town… Unique in its own way and brings back a lot of France culture to the Charlotte Uptown mix…!

The reason of my two star rating is because the service was so slow and also they were not very friendly. It seemed there was a chaos behind the counter. The pastry was not bad, but they were not exceptional. Overpriced on the drinks side as Starbucks has a better coffee/espresso and selection. Limited parking as well.
No, just no. The macrons are not good. If you have any self respect skip.

Fun decor & pastry case looks amazing but this place is mid at best. Not a true French patisserie but a watered down kitschy American version. Not sure anything is actually made in house?  Coffees & pastries turned out to be a major disappoint and service was poor. Won’t be back and really don’t recommend if looking for good coffee & pastries.

The atmosphere is really good. The service is slow. We stopped in for a quick snack and coffee. After seeing flies landing on the food, we lost our appetite and just got coffee only. I mentioned it to the lady behind the counter, and she said she would take care of it, yet they kept serving the food with flies. You lost my business for sure.

I have pictures, but can't see anyplace to upload while leaving this review.
Delicious and a cool vibe!

We ordered a French dip sandwich. $11.25. The sandwich had 2 thin sliced pieces of roast beef that were dry as a board. Swiss cheese that was barely there. The entire sandwich was only half an inch thick which was mostly bread. It was cold as well. Very disappointed. Do better.

A must stop when I'm in Charlotte! I usually go to a different location, but this one was just as good! They were pretty busy, but the service was still pretty quick! We tried a few different varieties of macaroons, fruit tarts, and the pecan tart was amazing! Great bakery if you're in the area!
Amazing and Beautiful!  It's just always freezing and you can't enjoy too much time there. 🙄

Going this place from beginning to end, they have improved step by step , quality is awesome

Have people in Charlotte never had good food? The reviews on here are wild. I’ve gotten better baked goods and desserts at Whole Foods. They don’t even look pretty and that’s the whole point of patisserie (have y’all not watched Bake-off)? Says a lot about the food scene here… very underwhelming.

reviews_data.review_text: Definitely have to get the chocolate croissant and ask to heat it up a lil bit. Of course you have to get it with a coffee! Personally, their fruit tarts are my fav. They're packed with blue berries, strawberries, and some kiwi!
Easy to order online but coffee is not good. Haven’t tried any of the food though!

We waited in line while a worker counted items in the case rather than waiting on a customer. I asked how do we order and she said two names of people we don’t know chatted incessantly to other customers. The napoleon I got was one of the worst I have ever had and I have eaten them for 50 years. This is the second and last time I will frequent this business. I have no idea why people like it. Your service was horrible, I imagine this was a manger. I thought you might help us but no, you basically said I don’t care just wait.

Lovely popping French ambience with a wide variety of delicious, high quality pastries and beverages with decent portions and slightly above average prices ($5-6 for pastries and $3-4 for small beverages). They have ample seating, Wi-Fi and good restrooms.

Our favorites were the creme brulee (not too sweet), espresso bomb (great flavor and very smooth) and the chai latte (perfect sweetness and flavor).

The tiramisu latte was also good but was a bit sweeter than expected.

They have a large variety of macaroons too.

Great coffee
Too pricey for everything though

Mediocre French goodies.. always a long line.  Staff is haphazard and unorganized. Wasn't super happy to learn that they don't actually make a lot of the stuff there, and there isn't anything French about them at all. Talk about cultural appropriation for profit.
In Charlotte for the weekend! Absolutely amazing! Tried multiple pastries! The coffee! All the things! Beautiful place! Great service! So quirky and fun! Loved it all!!!!
5 star biscuit breakfast sandwich. Almost a cross between a biscuit and croissant. Coffee is top notch. Everything is good
Cute french bakery with a lot of art references  and decor. The ambiance is lovely. The coffee was great. However, the tiramisu and creme brulee were too sweet for my taste.

Wow! This new location and employees are incredible. I have been a customer of Amélie’s for 13 years, but this most recent experience with the wonderful employee, Natasha, has been the best! She was patient and answered questions about the macarons, and then went above and beyond by helping me keep the flavors straight in a labeled box. I am so grateful.
So many yummy desserts 😋  Loved the macaroons 😍
Cashier attitude a tad unfriendly. Bakery, nice presentation but very underwhelming taste. Sandwiches not very tasty. Turkey over salted and small bread slices. Very cool decoration. Good coffee.

Macarons were delicious. Also got a strawberry dome shaped dessert that I forget the name of. Fiancé and I got coffee and the kids got lemonades. All of it was delicious and the staff was very friendly and helpful.

The place is beautiful, the paintings, the decoration, the food very delicious, the desserts unique but the bathrooms very dirty. They must be more careful. What's the point of a beautiful restaurant with disgusting bathrooms???
Amelie's has the best desserts and I love the Eiffel Tower décor in the back.

My company hired Amelie’s to cater a professional event we were hosting. From the moment we engaged their services, they were wonderful to work with, and made the planning process extremely easy. Anytime I had questions, they were quick to respond and always friendly and kind. On the day of the event, they showed up early and arranged the food and beverages on the tables in a perfect manner. Their prices were far superior to any local catering company, and we would absolutely hire them again for our next event.

The salted caramel brownie is delicious, but it's rich. I had difficulty eating it in one sitting, but that left me with leftovers.

The coffee is really good, but the barista was on the slow side.
Friendly staff, GREAT atmosphere, and the BEST pastries and desserts in Charlotte!! The fruit yogurt tart is my favorite!
Took my wife and 2 daughters atmosphere was chillax patrons were laid back staff was friendly smiling dope vibes and an inviting place to do some work ,conversations, or night cap
It was a fun experience with delicious treats.

The service was good and so was my pastry. However, at the time of my visit (10:30pm Friday, April 19th), there was a pungent odor of sewage. I've never experienced it before and there were no signs explaining it. Even when I sat in the back room, I could  smell it.
Very neat spot. Lots of ambience and very tasty pastries.

The desserts are okay. Coffee is really average. Matcha latte wasn’t good at all.
Floors and tables aren’t cleaned off had to walk around to find a clean table.
I love Amelie’s!!! They have such good food and pastries, my favorite place to study!! Although their bathrooms are gross and really need to be cleaned 😔

Incompetent service, ordered a drink and never received it. Told the cashier didn’t properly submit it and I would have to get back in line. Very disappointing.

However the food that I did receive that was properly rang up was good so silver lining.
So, many fabulous looking treats. I had the strawberry creme tart 😋.  If I lived there it would be a once aweek stop.
While visiting Charlotte we stopped here Sunday morning for coffee and ended up with an Almond Croissant and Quiche Lorraine. Both were very good and the coffee was good as well. Recommend!

This bakery has a great atmosphere. They have a fantastic selection of pastries. It is a little pricey but the quality of the food and the decorum of the bakery makes it well worth it. We have been back many times.
Loved the decor. Coffee was great and so was their Crème Brûlée.

Must Try pastries

This place is a bit overrated. The pastries are ok. They are somewhat overpriced in my opinion, and I've never been too blown away over anything that I've tried. I absolutely love this place and anytime I go in here I always spend over $50 in pastries to bring home to my family. I went there yesterday and bought a dozen macarons. I almost broke a took on the birthday cake cookie and then went for another and the entire shell on  both sides just shattered and went everywhere. I’m just disappointed because I don’t live in town, so going to this bakery is always something I look forward to and I’m just going to stop wasting my money on food that can’t be eaten

The manager Brain very rude person, this place not children friendly,I have very bad experience with them.
Hermoso todo!

This place is awesome! I have to say the creme brûlée and tiramisu was the best i have had! The atmosphere was great and it was decorated really cool. Seems like a great cafe to come and do a little work at as well. Can’t wait to go back and try more treats!

Everything we tried: croissant, salted caramel brownie, tiramisu, lemon raspberry tart, crème brûlée, and salted caramel mocha

10/10 recommend the treats.

Do not recommend the bathrooms unless you really gotta go. they were not very clean and the sinks were super small i could barely wash my hands without touching some part of the sink. Had to walk into three bathrooms before selecting so there is not regular cleaning (and seemingly some inconsiderate customers)

I have never had an issue with Amelie's. So it is very disappointing to share the experience I had this morning.  Bright and early at 7 AM I went there to get something to eat.  Immediately, it seemed as though young girl with the ponytail this morning, 7 AM, was not very happy that I didn't know exactly what I wanted, immediately. More importantly, when I received my order, which was the blueberry muffin that was warmed.  The same girl young girl with the ponytail, took the item out of the oven, put it in plastic container, walked toward the cashier and....just held her hand out. I repeat, Just held her hand out. My son and I was standing away from the front counter, about 3 meters. She said nothing. My son whom I didn't get to stop in time, walked over to her to get it. Which, of course, she said nothing. Not thank you, not Have a nice day. Nothing.
My son took the plastic container from her hand and, picked up the other plastic container on the counter.  Once we were on our way, he realized it was not the right order.  So, sometime this morning Amelie's must have realized a French Toast order was not received. Whose fault is that? The young girl with the ponytail from the 7am shift this morning.
We all have days we're tired or such. However, Customer Service  is of most importance. I'm not sure what excuse Ms. Young Lady has, but I do hope I will not experience this anymore. Amelie's has always been a fav of mine.

reviews_data.review_text:
Amélie’s is a staple — a Charlotte institution with genuinely great food. The pastries are excellent, the coffee is solid, and the kitchen clearly knows what it’s doing. But the management and operations are embarrassingly bad.

There’s no online order pickup system. You order ahead thinking it’ll be ready — nope. You show up and your food hasn’t even been started. The café is always empty because by the time your order’s ready, you’ve already wasted your lunch break and have to leave.

The staff seems lost, the process is nonexistent, and there’s zero urgency. It feels like no one’s in charge.

It’s heartbreaking — because with even halfway competent leadership, this place would be unbeatable. Instead, it’s the last place I’ll go if I’m on a schedule.

Love the food. Hate the experience. Do better, Amélie’s.
Beyond beautiful interior as well as the desserts. The chocolate desserts are to die for! If I could eat here everyday I would. They have coffee and food as well.

I've always enjoyed Amélie's food, but this was my first and last time visiting this particular location. The selection of tarts and macaroons we tried were all delicious, but the employee taking our order and checking us out was downright rude. He was extremely impatient, not particularly knowledgeable about the menu, and even said "Just tell me what you want" when I asked a question about the menu.
Wonderful!
This place is incredible! Well worth a stop. It's nothing like I thought it would be, in the best way! Hope to be back next time :)

I frequent this location in NoDa & will continue to do so based on great atmosphere and customer service. One night I arrived about twenty minutes until closing; although I came in last minute after work, not once did I feel rushed or uncomfortable. In fact, the employees were very kind and understanding. I ordered a sundried tomato turkey wrap, chips, and some macarons. Everything was delicious as usual, however some desserts are touch and feel. For example, I love their Crookie (croissant cookie) and their Pistachio macarons! On the other hand, their chocolate pudding with chocolate chip layers (that is topped with a chocolate covered strawberry) looks very appetizing but falls short in taste. A lot of the desserts are touch and feel in the sense that some look good and taste mediocre, whereas some look underwhelming but taste delicious. This obviously is based on preference. I’m still going to frequent quite often because trying new items every visit has been fun! Shout out to their amazing staff ✨

I told management and they were very apologetic. Even had the kitchen manager come to table to discuss. They even adjusted the bill and asked it there was anything more they could do.
In my opinion , this is the way to address business concerns They get an “A” for customer service.

When you first walk in you are met with a whimsical scenery of Paris-inspired decor, a macaron inspired modle or a giant half of The Eiffle Tower, and you just know this is going to be a great experience.

The gentleman eho assisted us was knowledgeable and even threw in a suggestion of his own, which sounded fantastic.

I tried the salted caramel brownie, his suggestion. It was delicious with just enough caramel and brownie synergy to make the perfect dessert. I also tried the Marie Antoinette tart. They were delicate and tasteful and had a nice fresh raspberry compote on top. Then I tried the brownie cheesecake tart. This was my favorite one as I'm a sucker for brownies. I tried the Cafe Marcotter, which was heavy and filling, I only had half of the cup because of this. The taste was lovely with the French Vanilla. Finally, I had the Sundried Tomato Turkey Wrap which I felt could have been left off. It was something I could easily make at home, so it was nothing special.

Overall, I give this place a solid A+ for being so damn good!

I’ve been to Amélie’s multiple times, mostly for the macarons or crème brûlée, which are always solid. The pastries are definitely the highlight here! That said, the hot food items and salads don’t quite hit the mark for me, which is why I wouldn’t give it a full five stars. I’ve also noticed an off-putting smell on a couple of visits, though thankfully, that hasn’t been an issue recently. Still, the atmosphere is really cute, and it’s a nice spot to grab a sweet treat.

Amélie's French Bakery & Café offers a delightful culinary experience that truly captures the essence of French indulgence. The food is nothing short of superb — from the buttery, flaky croissants to the decadent pastries that melt in your mouth. Every bite feels like a trip to a charming Parisian pâtisserie.

The atmosphere is quaint and elegant, blending a cozy café charm with upscale European-inspired décor. It's the kind of place where you could linger with a book or chat with friends over cappuccinos in style.

The staff interaction occasionally felt curt, almost as though they were eager to move things along. While efficient, a warmer, more welcoming touch would elevate the experience significantly.

Despite the service hiccup, Amélie’s remains a gem for food lovers seeking an authentic taste of France in a beautiful setting.

When I asked about my order at the 25 minute mark, I was shown the dining room (that was less than half full) and was told they are very busy. At that point it became a matter of principle to me to find out how long it actually takes.

There's nothing wrong with being busy. I just wish they were upfront about it.

Sandwich was nothing to write home about.

Always a great experience! Got the pecan tarte, the crust is very crunchy, I think it would be better warmed but loved the caramelized pecans! The cheesecake brownie was also good, the brownie is so decadent! The “cheesecake” part on top wasn’t my favorite though. Still awesome atmosphere!
This place has a great ambience that transports one to Paris. It has quite a vibe with several Parisian props. Crème brûlée was great.

Wow, it's hard to believe that this is the same place it was before the ownership turned over
The pastries are sparse and, frankly, really unimpressive compared to the original location and owners vision.

That's bad enough, but let me tell you about the employees

I brought a friend in for his first time to Amelies. He was super excited and told the guy at the counter that it was first time in.
The guy responded, and I quote,  "That means *nothing* to me."
When I made small talk about loving the former location, he went on a very angry tirade about how terrible the hours were  and said directly to me - as if I had any input in, or control over this at all - that employees deserve outside lives too.
Well, of course they do. But yelling at two people who just want a croissant ain't gonna help anything.

We just left.
I had also just come in after learning that a friend had passed, so being screamed at by a stranger was especially awful.

Ordinary bland pastries and pissed off employees ?
Never again.

I fell in love with Amelie’s years ago. I recall wishing that they would open a location  in my hometown of Atlanta, GA they did, but it did not last long.

One night while  in Charlotte I made the suggestion that my family and I make a late night run to Amelie’s.  It’s been such a long time since I visited that I did not realize they are in a new location. The new  to me location still gives me the same energy as when I visited years ago. The quirkiness of the decor really makes this place special.

We arrived fairly late- maybe 30 minutes prior to closing. However, we were still able to order everything we wanted. Additionally, the staff still had great attitudes!

Overall I love everything about Amelie’s, the decor, the staff and most importantly the food and drinks. If you have a chance to check this spot out, I highly recommend. You do so!

Took a trip to Charlotte & this was a spot to try when visiting. Never had macaroons before, so I decided to try some and man it was delicious! They had so many variety of flavors ( PB&J is fav) . I also ordered the Buttermilk sausage sandwich…. THE BEST BISCUIT EVERR!

Who makes matcha with clots?? That’s insane

Fourth time here, fourth time my food is delayed or made wrong. The girl who first took my order was visibly upset and had just cursed at a coworker as I walked up to the register.

i got a lavender macaron, palmier, croissant, and a pistachio coconut latte. the latte, macaron, and croissant were all lovely but the palmier tasted a little stale to me. the woman at the cash register was rude when i asked for a drink recommendation. overall, i liked the vibe and the cafe itself is expansive with some interesting decorations/art

I 💓💓💓💓💓💓 this place! My friend and I stumbled upon this sweet place. Good food, little pricey, friendly service. The atmosphere was amazing!

This is one of my wife’s favorite places!

Came to this lovely place today and  sure glad I did the 2 men working were fast and had great recommendations i will definitely return

I was skeptical when my girl wanted to try this place but it was the most solid place I've been to in Charlotte. The crowd was diversified the decor was so perfect the at was wonderful.
Then there was the first omg you have to try the macaroons so go in give it a 10 hands down

I love this bakery! When I visit my son and his wife in Charlotte we have breakfast there.  Everything about it is so enjoyable.  The food, the staff, the decor.  You feel like you’re in Paris!

Amelie's is always tasty, I appreciate thr salted caramel brownie always being around and a rotation of macaron flavors to mix it up.
My favorite cafe in Charlotte! Fabulous vibe, friendly staff, chick atmosphere! You’ll love here!!
Great atmosphere and good selections. They lose two stars for requiring that I tip for two coffees when I paid with Apple Pay.

Dessert is my thing, and Amelie's didn't disappoint! Seriously, everything was scrumptious. Visit them!!! (And, I'm a baker who is very particular about the dessert I eat!) I just have to mention how adorbs it is inside. 😍😍😍

We came here for brunch around 1 PM on a Saturday. The line was decently long but we only waited about ten minutes. The staff were knowledgeable and friendly!

We each got a tiramisu latte & split the lemon raspberry tart. I got the cream cheese danish and my friend got the strawberry danish.

The lattes were so creamy & smooth! The tart was creamy and fluffy. The strawberry danish had super fresh strawberries and was drizzled in honey. The cream cheese on both was beautifully rich & the pastry was fluffy with the perfect amount of crisp on the edges.

The macaroon flavors we got were (from top to bottom, left to right): Lavender Lemon, Café au lait, Cookie Dough, RE&B (proceeds toward the Hurricane Helene Fund), PB&J, and Coconut Lime. We weren’t sure of the flavor of the Red, White, & Blue but it reminded of us crunch berries! Super tasty.

Can’t wait to try other items on my next visit!

Amélie's French Bakery & Café. It's an absolute gem that never fails to impress! During my recent visit, I treated myself to their crème brûlée and fruit tart, and let me tell you, they were both out of this world. The crème brûlée had the perfect caramelized top, giving way to a luscious, velvety custard underneath. And the fruit tart? It was a masterpiece with its buttery, flaky crust and a colorful array of fresh fruits that provided a delightful contrast to the creamy filling.

And let's not forget about their coffee - it's the perfect companion to their desserts, with its rich flavor balancing out the sweetness. Yes, the location might be a bit tricky to find, but trust me, the search is totally worth it. Whenever I'm in Charlotte, Amélie's is a non-negotiable stop for me. The consistently top-notch treats and the cozy atmosphere make it an absolute must-visit!
Great pastries. The coffee could been better. I had cappuccino and it was super weak and watery.

Loved it to the bits. Charlotte being a new city, Amelie’s was on the top recommendations on the list of things to do. The place gives a fancy vibe yet simple enough to feel comfortable instantly. The desserts have a good variety and will definitely want to keep going back to try more/all of it… Also, they have very good vegetarian options for meals - which is a huge plus. Definitely a recommended spot if you are in town… Unique in its own way and brings back a lot of France culture to the Charlotte Uptown mix…!
